import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['width'], data['height'], c=data['values'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Width')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the width and height of volcano eruptions?')
    plt.colorbar(label='Eruption Value')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average value of volcano eruptions?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Values")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from datetime import datetime

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['values'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Volcano Eruption Values')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values by year?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import json
import urllib.request

# Load data from URL
url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GizemYaylaci/visualization/main/volcano.json'
response = urllib.request.urlopen(url)
data = pd.read_json(response.read())

# Create scatter plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
ax.scatter(data['width'], data['height'], c=data['values'], cmap='YlOrRd', alpha=0.8)

# Set chart title and axis labels
ax.set_title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values by location?', wrap=True)
ax.set_xlabel('Width')
ax.set_ylabel('Height')

# Add colorbar
cbar = plt.colorbar()
cbar.set_label('Values')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```
